Name: autosomal dominant limb-girdle muscular dystrophy type 1H
Definition: An autosomal dominant limb-girdle muscular dystrophy that has_material_basis_in with variation in the region 3p25.1-p23.

Name: autosomal dominant limb-girdle muscular dystrophy type 2
Definition: An autosomal dominant limb-girdle muscular dystrophy that has_material_basis_in heterozygous mutation in the TNPO3 gene on chromosome 7q32.

Name: autosomal dominant limb-girdle muscular dystrophy type 1
Definition: An autosomal dominant limb-girdle muscular dystrophy that has_material_basis_in heterozygous mutation in the DNAJB6 gene on chromosome 7q36.

Name: autosomal dominant limb-girdle muscular dystrophy type 3
Definition: An autosomal dominant limb-girdle muscular dystrophy that has_material_basis_in heterozygous mutation in the HNRNPDL gene on chromosome 4q21.
